      <p>When the documented steps don&rsquo;t hold, the cause is usually past the surface &mdash; a permission or UAC configuration that re-blocks the update after each reboot, security software that quarantines the file again, an install that needs repair, or update-component damage that a clean re-download alone won&rsquo;t fix. A Certified ProAdvisor with active Desktop and Enterprise certifications diagnoses the actual root cause, fixes it against a written scope, and verifies the update completes cleanly before closing. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s software support.</p>
